</p></section><section id="GUID-1156E15C-FA11-42F7-80CE-F9823F371FA9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Function</title><p class="- topic/p ">This test enables you to disable a printhead. 
</p><note id="GUID-5EC6AD8F-EB49-4E8D-91CD-626CC2522B12" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">You must be in zero SDS. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-92369981-F020-4E62-9707-58F93D054214" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Description</title><p class="- topic/p ">Disabling a printhead prevents permanent errors due to a broken printhead. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">After a reboot of the printer the printheads are automatically enabled again. When the wrong printhead is disabled, select it again. 
